  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct used in lumbar spinal fusion procedures. The FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two independent laboratories under ASTM F1717 loading conditions. All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed; one factor (Test conditions) falls below the required level due to a single test condition being evaluated. The intended use scope — pre-market submission support for a Class II spinal implant system — is described throughout the Claim and Requirement documentation referenced herein. Model risk level is assessed as 3 (Medium-High) consistent with the decision outcome of Accepted at Medium assurance.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/req/f1717-compression-bending-fea-prediction",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/claim/fea-predicts-f1717-static-performance",
